Kemi Olunloyo made an observation on her Facebook page about Abba Kyari, the indicted Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP) who was suspended and charged in court for his illegal dealings with criminals.

ALSO READ: Abba Kyari marks 47th birthday in NDLEA custody
According to journalist Kemi Olunloyo, DCP Abba Kyari’s birthday was on Thursday, the 3rd of March 2022, but something seemed off on his social media page. She revealed that on DCP Abba Kyari’s regular birthday, he would get over 20k comments wishing him a happy birthday.
However, DCP Abba Kyari didn’t get such treatment from people when he had his birthday in 2022 after his indictment for fraud and drug-related offenses. Kemi Olunloyo opined that everyone has deserted the once revered policeman, as he no longer receives super-cop praises.

ALSO READ: ‘All these actors fainting’ — Kate Henshaw taunt DCP Kyari’s wife
Kemi Olunloyo reminded people of her casual advice to them, that they shouldn’t let people praise them because the same people would be happy if there was a downfall. According to her, she gives herself praise as she waits for no one to give her praise. See her post below.



